{{Youmay|a pre-[[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] [[Philosopher/Legends|philosopher]]|[[Octa Ramis]], a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] of the [[New Jedi Order]]}}
'''Dak Ramis''' was a [[Philosopher/Legends|philosopher]] and thinker who came to prominence some [[Time/Legends|time]] before the formation of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], [[25,053 BBY|over 25,000 years]] before the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Ramis' ideas were well known, and the philosopher was sometimes mentioned in the same vein of [[Plaristes]].<ref name="Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref>

The teachings of Dak Ramis were a great influence to [[Darth Millennial]] when he was developing the [[Dark Force]] religion.<ref name="Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties" />

